column5: Totem lodegs has three parts to it there is Totem,Yellowbird,and Wiley point lodge its a bite on the expensive side but you get treated well, food is good they get new boats every year and have some great guides. The only down fall is they book up early and some times over book and people get stuck with substandard guides which can make for a bad trip. Try to book when its slower,peak times for them is june and sept. so you may try july and august. If your interested try this web site it will give you other choices in the area.www.lakeofthewoods.com
